data.title: Income
data.name: Factors that increase risk of infection and severe illness
data.intent: “This is more than about race”
data.description: Californians in crowded housing or transportation, and with less access to paid leave and other worker protections, have a higher risk of infection of COVID-19. Social determinants of health, such as food insecurity, lack of health insurance, and housing instability can increase the risk of poor outcomes. These social determinants of health are often the result of structural racism.

data.title: Equity metric - test positivity
data.name: COVID-19 health equity metric
data.intent: “This is so important that we use this to determine a county’s reopening” (so that everyone is brought along)
data.description: The health equity metric measures the positivity rate in the most disproportionately-impacted communities. These communities are identified in the Healthy Places Index as census tracts that have less healthy community conditions such as low median income, education completeness, and health care access. The Blueprint for a Safer Economy ensures that counties address COVID-19 in all communities. To open further, the health equity metric cannot significantly fall behind overall county positivity rates.
data_publishing_system: Snowflake data pulled by FaaS script and published to Github
data.metric: Testing positivity in the lowest 25% of the healthy places HE index, by county
data.data_attributes_/_options:
- Test positivity rate
- Lowest 25% healthy HE index

data.title: Vaccination by Groups: Race and Ethnicity
data.name: People with at least one dose of vaccine administered by race and ethnicity in California
data.intent:
The distribution of first vaccine doses by race and ethnicity, age, and gender is shown below. Providing this information is voluntary and not required for vaccination. 

Initially, vaccination was limited to healthcare workers and long-term care residents. Hence the data reflects those populations more than other California residents. Data shows the cumulative total administered and are updated daily.

data.title: Daily cases and deaths, Total confirmed cases, Episode date
data.name: Daily cases and deaths
data.intent: Daily cases and deaths, Total confirmed cases, Episode date
data.description: California confirmed cases and deaths.
data_publishing_system: Snowflake data pulled by FaaS script and published to Github
data.data_methodology: Note: Numbers do not represent true day-over-day changes as these results include cases from prior to yesterday. Episode date is the date the event is estimated to have taken place. Reported date is the date the event was reported to the California Department of Public Health. Cases includes people in state and federal prisons, US Immigration and Customs Enforcement facilities, US Marshal detention facilities, and Department of State Hospitals facilities. These groups are excluded from the Blueprint tier assignment calculations, which show different case and test positivity rates. A negative number of reported deaths means that deaths previously attributed to COVID-19 were determined to not be associated with COVID-19.

data.title: Testing for COVID-19, Total tests, Testing date
data.name: Testing for COVID-19
data.intent: Testing for COVID-19, Total tests, Testing date
data.description: The number of COVID-19 diagnostic test results in California.
data_publishing_system: Snowflake data pulled by FaaS script and published to Github
data.data_methodology: Note: Testing date is the date the test was administered. Reported date is the date the event was reported to the California Department of Public Health. Reported date data is not available for tests before May 5, 2020. Testing date data excludes out-of-state and unknown jurisdiction tests and total numbers may not match reporting date numbers. Positivity rate is calculated as the number of positive molecular tests divided by the total molecular tests performed. Positivity rate includes people in state and federal prisons, US Immigration and Customs Enforcement facilities, US Marshal detention facilities, and Department of State Hospitals facilities. These groups are excluded from the Blueprint tier assignment calculations, which show different case and test positivity rates. Positivity rate was previously reported as a 14-day average.
